        "id": 2363220,
        "name": "Tom Reddick",
        "username": "Tom_Reddick",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/ecb155/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-02-21T04:46:39.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Good evening all,</p>\n<p>Recently got reliable access to a decent allocation of this as part of my search to bring a little bit of \u201cold school\u201d CA Cab back into the cellar, and curious to know between the 2012 and 2013 which might be more approachable young? I have never had this particular wine from Corison, and so I really must taste one in the near future even though I imagine it is a long term wine.</p>\n<p>Based on other recent experience, I would think the 2012- but again, never having tried this, I would be grateful for thoughts from someone who has had both vintages. Gilman certainly raved about both, but I did not get a good sense of which might be more approachable now from his notes.</p>\n<p>Any advance opening or double decanting advice most welcome too. I have a few fond memories of the regular Corison from years back, so I am very excited to give this wine a try.</p>\n<p>Many thanks in advance.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 11,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-03T03:14:13.895Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
