        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"ky1em!ttskus\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n ky1em!ttskus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"c fu\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n c fu:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I always thought the Kronos bottling strayed from the more restrained style of corison.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Cathy only does two CS bottlings under the Corison label and Kronos is her estate vineyard. My guess that it would represent her desired style more than the Napa bottling, no?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>i dunno, the ones I\u2019ve had have been very forward and ripe. I used to drink a lot of it since my bud was a huge Corison collector. But it\u2019s been at least a good 4-5 years since I\u2019ve had one.</p>",
